Damh (pronounced dav) is a merry god of satyrs and their cousins, the long-haired feral korreds, and also atomies. 
Damh loves dancing, song, music, bardic verse, jesters, and strong drink. He especially loves dryads. He is a very old deity, said to have helped build the first stone circles and raised standing stones. He has strong associations with stone, rock, and the earth itself, and he is a guardian as well.
He carries a set of pipes, a wooden flute, and a harp. He is chaotic neutral.
Source: Monster Mythology